  "text": "ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable is defined in raft/storage.go as a sentinel error returned when a snapshot is temporarily unavailable. During Raft log catch-up, when a follower node falls too far behind and a leader needs to send snapshots to help it rejoin the cluster, the snapshot availability check is implemented in raft/raft.go. The maybeSendSnapshot function is called during the append entries flow (from sendAppend and maybeSendAppend). When attempting to send a snapshot to a peer that needs catching up, if the Storage.Snapshot() call returns ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable, the leader gracefully handles this by logging a debug message and returning false, effectively pausing the snapshot sending attempt. This allows the system to retry later without panicking, providing resilience when snapshots are not immediately available during node rejoin scenarios."
}

